# Line-ending normalization (QA-26).
#
# legacy-design-tools is developed on a mix of Windows and Linux
# clones, several with `core.autocrlf=true`. Without a `.gitattributes`
# that produced recurring phantom CRLF-only diffs and content-empty
# stashes that repeatedly bit cc-agent sessions. `text=auto eol=lf`
# stores LF in the repo and checks out LF everywhere, which overrides
# a clone's autocrlf setting and makes line endings deterministic.
#
# Note: this normalizes line endings going forward only. A one-time
# repo-wide `git add --renormalize .` to rewrite already-committed
# CRLF blobs is intentionally NOT done here (it would be pure,
# unreviewable churn) — see the cleanup-batch session report.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize line endings.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.webp  binary
*.avif  binary
*.pdf   binary
*.glb   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.eot   binary
*.zip   binary
*.gz    binary
*.wasm  binary
*.node  binary
